description.text: Description on how to recycle the garment

submodelElements.value:
Reduce e-waste: Consider upgrading hardware or software instead of buying a new product, and teach kids about e-waste.
Don't mix e-waste with household waste: Don't put e-waste in wet or dry waste bins, or give it to informal sectors like rag pickers.
Remove batteries: Remove any batteries, and lithium-ion batteries should not go in household garbage or recycling bins.
Delete personal information: Delete all personal information from your electronics.
Find a recycling center: Many retailers offer free recycling schemes or take-back options. You can also check your postcode on a recycling locator tool to find the nearest recycling center that accepts waste electronics.
Give it to a local organization: Find a reliable local organization who will recycle it
